643
00:55:13,160 --> 00:55:17,880
To reiterate, every pair of antipodal points on the two sphere

644
00:55:17,880 --> 00:55:24,280
is just one point in RP2. We can write this in the language of

645
00:55:24,280 --> 00:55:29,640
equivalence relations by saying that RP2 is s2 modulo the

646
00:55:29,640 --> 00:55:34,200
equivalence relation that the point x, y, z is the same as

647
00:55:34,200 --> 00:55:40,440
negative x, negative y, negative z. Now, this construction directly extends

648
00:55:40,440 --> 00:55:45,880
to the three sphere. So, RP3 is just s3 modulo the equivalence

649
00:55:45,880 --> 00:55:49,480
relation that antipodal points on the three sphere

650
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:55,160
are identified with each other. The relevance this has for us is that

651
00:55:55,160 --> 00:56:01,160
topologically, s03 is RP3. This goes hand in hand with

652
00:56:01,160 --> 00:56:05,480
s2 being s3 and gives us another way to understand

653
00:56:05,480 --> 00:56:10,440
how s02 is the double cover of s03.

654
00:56:10,760 --> 00:56:16,040
On the subject of this covering space business, let me point out that while

655
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:21,400
the fundamental group of s03 is z mod2, the fundamental group of s02

656
00:56:21,400 --> 00:56:24,760
is the trivial group, the group with only one element, which is because all

657
00:56:24,760 --> 00:56:28,120
paths can be contracted on the three sphere.

658
00:56:28,120 --> 00:56:32,840
Note that the fundamental group of s03 then has twice the number of elements

659
00:56:32,840 --> 00:56:37,480
as the fundamental group of s02. This fact is intimately related to the

660
00:56:37,480 --> 00:56:43,720
fact that s02 is a double cover of s03 and not, say, a triple cover.

